2. ADDING REPOSITORIES TO A PRODUCT
================================================================

Based on a typical Ubuntu Noble (24.04) sources.list, repeat
these steps for each repository entry.

Step 1:  Go to Content --> Products --> [Your Product Name]

Step 2:  Click the "Repositories" tab.

Step 3:  Click "New Repository".

Step 4:  Fill in the repository details:

         --- Example 1: noble main ---
         Name          : noble-main
         Type          : deb
         URL           : http://us.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/
         Releases      : noble
         Components    : main restricted
         Architectures : amd64

         --- Example 2: noble-updates ---
         Name          : noble-updates
         Type          : deb
         URL           : http://us.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/
         Releases      : noble-updates
         Components    : main restricted
         Architectures : amd64

         --- Example 3: noble universe ---
         Name          : noble-universe
         Type          : deb
         URL           : http://us.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/
         Releases      : noble
         Components    : universe
         Architectures : amd64

         --- Example 4: noble-updates universe ---
         Name          : noble-updates-universe
         Type          : deb
         URL           : http://us.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/
         Releases      : noble-updates
         Components    : universe
         Architectures : amd64

         --- Example 5: noble multiverse ---
         Name          : noble-multiverse
         Type          : deb
         URL           : http://us.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/
         Releases      : noble
         Components    : multiverse
         Architectures : amd64

         --- Example 6: noble-updates multiverse ---
         Name          : noble-updates-multiverse
         Type          : deb
         URL           : http://us.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/
         Releases      : noble-updates
         Components    : multiverse
         Architectures : amd64

         --- Example 7: noble-backports ---
         Name          : noble-backports
         Type          : deb
         URL           : http://us.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/
         Releases      : noble-backports
         Components    : main restricted universe multiverse
         Architectures : amd64

         --- Example 8: noble-security main ---
         Name          : noble-security-main
         Type          : deb
         URL           : http://security.ubuntu.com/ubuntu
         Releases      : noble-security
         Components    : main restricted
         Architectures : amd64

         --- Example 9: noble-security universe ---
         Name          : noble-security-universe
         Type          : deb
         URL           : http://security.ubuntu.com/ubuntu
         Releases      : noble-security
         Components    : universe
         Architectures : amd64

         --- Example 10: noble-security multiverse ---
         Name          : noble-security-multiverse
         Type          : deb
         URL           : http://security.ubuntu.com/ubuntu
         Releases      : noble-security
         Components    : multiverse
         Architectures : amd64

Step 5:  Click "Save" after each repository entry.

Step 6:  Repeat Steps 3-5 for every repository you want to add.


